<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-15T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-15T18:36:00-05:00" n="978" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d978">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/218.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-15T17:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It is impossible for the arms and ammunition committee of the American
                            colony organisation to secure sufficient arms and ammunition for their
                            purposes. They have formally requested me to ascertain from our
                            Government whether 500 rifles, with necessary ammunition, can be sold,
                            loaned or given to the organization, and, if sold, at what price. Are
                            there not some Krag-Jorgensens out of use at San Antonio? The governor
                            of the Federal District is well disposed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>